obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (3983)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3983&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the National Green Tribunal Act,`
  line 2010.
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 18th October, 2010, vide notification No. S.O 2569(E), dated 18th October, 2010, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (3984)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3984&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "accident" means an accident involving a fortuitous or sudden or unintended occurrence`
  line `while handling any hazardous substance or equipment, or plant, or vehicle resulting in continuous or`
  line `intermittent or repeated exposure to death, of, or, injury to, any person or damage to any property or`
  line `environment but does not include an accident by reason only of war or civil disturbance;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chairperson" means the Chairperson of the National Green Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(c) "environment" includes water, air and land and the inter-relationship, which exists among and`
  line `between water, air and land and human beings, other living creatures, plants, micro-organism and`
  line property;
  line
  line `(d) "Expert Member" means a member of the Tribunal who, is appointed as such, and holds`
  line `qualifications specified in sub-section (2) of section 5, and, is not a Judicial Member;`
  line
  line `(e) "handling", in relation to any hazardous substance, means the manufacture, processing,`
  line `treatment, package, storage, transportation, use, collection, destruction, conversion, offering for sale,`
  line `transfer or the like of such hazardous substance;`
  line
  line `(f) "hazardous substance" means any substance or preparation which is defined as hazardous`
  line `substance in the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986), and exceeding such quantity as`
  line `specified or may be specified by the Central Government under the Public Liability Insurance Act,`
  line `1991 (6 of 1991);`
  line
  line `(g) "injury" includes permanent, partial or total disablement or sickness resulting out of an`
  line accident;
  line
  line `(h) "Judicial Member" means a member of the Tribunal who is qualified to be appointed as such`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 5 and includes the Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(i) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(j) "person" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) an individual,`
  line
  line `(ii) a Hindu undivided family,`
  line
  line `(iii) a company,`
  line
  line `(iv) a firm,`
  line
  line `(v) an association of persons or a body of individuals, whether incorporated or not,`
  line
  line `(vi) trustee of a trust,`
  line
  line `(vii) a local authority, and`
  line
  line `(viii) every artificial juridical person, not falling within any of the preceding sub-clauses;`
  line
  line `(k) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(l) "Schedule" means Schedules I, II and III appended to this Act;`
  line
  line `(m) "substantial question relating to environment' shall include an instance where,--`
  line
  line `(i) there is a direct violation of a specific statutory environmental obligation by a person by`
  line which,--
  line
  line `(A) the community at large other than an individual or group of individuals is affected or`
  line `likely to be affected by the environmental consequences; or`
  line
  line `(B) the gravity of damage to the environment or property is substantial; or`
  line
  line `(C) the damage to public health is broadly measurable;`
  line
  line `(ii) the environmental consequences relate to a specific activity or a point source of pollution;`
  line
  line `(n) "Tribunal" means the National Green Tribunal established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(o) "workman" has the meaning assigned to it in the Workmen's Compensation Act, 1923 (8 of`
  line `1923).`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used in this Act but not defined herein and defined in the Water`
  line `(Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974 (6 of 1974), the Water (Prevention and Control of`
  line `Pollution) Cess Act, 1977 (36 of 1977), the Forest (Conservation) Act, 1980 (69 of 1980), the Air`
  line `(Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1981 (14 of 1981), the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986`
  line `(29 of 1986), the Public Liability Insurance Act, 1991 (6 of 1991) and the Biological Diversity Act, 2002`
  line `(18 of 2003) and other Acts relating to environment shall have the meaning, respectively, assigned to`
  line `them in those Acts.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (3985)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3985&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall, by notification, establish, with effect`
  line `from such date as may be specified therein, a Tribunal to be known as the National Green Tribunal to`
  line `exercise the jurisdiction, powers and authority conferred on such Tribunal by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (3986)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3986&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a full time Chairperson;`
  line
  line `(b) not less than ten but subject to maximum of twenty full time Judicial Members as the Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, notify;`
  line
  line `(c) not less than ten but subject to maximum of twenty full time Expert Members, as the Central`
  line `Government may, from time to time, notify.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson of the Tribunal may, if considered necessary, invite any one or more person`
  line `having specialised knowledge and experience in a particular case before the Tribunal to assist the`
  line `Tribunal in that case.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may, by notification, specify the ordinary place or places of sitting of`
  line `the Tribunal, and the territorial jurisdiction falling under each such place of sitting.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, in consultation with the Chairperson of the Tribunal, make rules`
  line `regulating generally the practices and procedure of the Tribunal including--`
  line
  line `(a) the rules as to the persons who shall be entitled to appear before the Tribunal;`
  line
  line `(b) the rules as to the procedure for hearing applications and appeals and other matters [including`
  line `the circuit procedure for hearing at a place other than the ordinary place of its sitting falling within the`
  line `jurisdiction referred to in sub-section (3)], pertaining to the applications and appeals;`
  line
  line `(c) the minimum number of Members who shall hear the applications and appeals in respect of`
  line `any class or classes of applications and appeals:`
  line
  line `Provided that the number of Expert Members shall, in hearing an application or appeal, be equal`
  line `to the number of Judicial Members hearing such application or appeal;`
  line
  line `(d) rules relating to transfer of cases by the Chairperson from one place of sitting (including the`
  line `ordinary place of sitting) to other place of sitting.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (3987)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Qualifications for appointment of Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3987&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as the Chairperson or Judicial Member of the Tribunal`
  line `unless he is, or has been, a Judge of the Supreme Court of India or Chief Justice of a High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that a person who is or has been a Judge of the High Court shall also be qualified to be`
  line `appointed as a Judicial Member.`
  line
  line `(2) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as an Expert Member, unless he,--`
  line
  line `(a) has a degree in Master of Science (in physical sciences or life sciences) with a Doctorate`
  line `degree or Master of Engineering or Master of Technology and has an experience of fifteen years in`
  line `the relevant field including five years practical experience in the field of environment and forests`
  line `(including pollution control, hazardous substance management, environment impact assessment,`
  line `climate change management, biological diversity management and forest conservation) in a reputed`
  line `National level institution; or`
  line
  line `(b) has administrative experience of fifteen years including experience of five years in dealing`
  line `with environmental matters in the Central or a State Government or in a reputed National or State`
  line `level institution.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member of the Tribunal shall not hold any other`
  line `office during their tenure as such.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairperson and other Judicial and Expert Members shall not, for a period of two years from`
  line `the date on which they cease to hold office, accept any employment in, or connected with the`
  line `management or administration of, any person who has been a party to a proceeding before the Tribunal`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall apply to any employment under the Central`
  line `Government or a State Government or local authority or in any statutory authority or any corporation`
  line `established by or under any Central, State or Provincial Act or a Government company as defined in`
  line `section 617 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (3988)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Appointment of Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3988&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the`
  line `provisions of section 5, the Chairperson, Judicial Members and Expert Members of the Tribunal shall be`
  line `appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson shall be appointed by the Central Government in consultation with the Chief`
  line `Justice of India.`
  line
  line `(3) The Judicial Members and Expert Members of the Tribunal shall be appointed on the`
  line `recommendations of such Selection Committee and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (3989)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Term of office and other conditions of service of Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3989&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member of the Tribunal shall hold office as`
  line `such for a term of five years from the date on which they enter upon their office, but shall not be eligible`
  line `for re-appointment:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case a person, who is or has been a Judge of the Supreme Court, has been appointed`
  line `as Chairperson or Judicial Member of the Tribunal, he shall not hold office after he has attained the age of`
  line `seventy years:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case a person, who is or has been the Chief Justice of a High Court, has been`
  line `appointed as Chairperson or Judicial Member of the Tribunal, he shall not hold office after he has attained`
  line `the age of sixty-seven years:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case a person, who is or has been a Judge of a High Court, has been appointed as`
  line `Judicial Member of the Tribunal, he shall not hold office after he has attained the age of sixty-seven`
  line `years:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no Expert Member shall hold office after he has attained the age of sixty-five`
  line years.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (3990)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Resignation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3990&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member of the Tribunal may, by`
  line `notice in writing under their hand addressed to the Central Government, resign their office.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (3991)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Salaries, allowances and other terms and conditions of service.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3991&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The salaries and allowances`
  line `payable to, and the other terms and conditions of service (including pension, gratuity and other retirement`
  line `benefits) of, the Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member of the Tribunal shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that neither the salary and allowances nor the other terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member shall be varied to their disadvantage after their`
  line appointment.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (3992)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Removal and suspension of Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3992&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Central Government may, in consultation with the Chief Justice of India, remove from office of the`
  line `Chairperson or Judicial Member of the Tribunal, who,--`
  line
  line `(a) has been adjudged an insolvent; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been convicted of an offence which, in the opinion of the Central Government, involves`
  line `moral turpitude; or`
  line
  line `(c) has become physically or mentally incapable; or`
  line
  line `(d) has acquired such financial or other interest as is likely to affect prejudicially his functions; or`
  line
  line `(e) has so abused his position as to render his continuance in office prejudicial to the public`
  line interest.
  line
  line `(2) The Chairperson or Judicial Member shall not be removed from his office except by an order`
  line `made by the Central Government after an inquiry made by a Judge of the Supreme Court in which such`
  line `Chairperson or Judicial Member has been informed of the charges against him and given a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard in respect of those charges.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may suspend from office the Chairperson or Judicial Member in respect`
  line `of whom a reference of conducting an inquiry has been made to the Judge of the Supreme Court under sub-section (2), until the Central Government passes an order on receipt of the report of inquiry made by`
  line `the Judge of the Supreme Court on such reference.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may, by rules, regulate the procedure for inquiry referred to in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(5) The Expert Member may be removed from his office by an order of the Central Government on`
  line `the grounds specified in sub-section (1) and in accordance with the procedure as may be notified by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Expert Member shall not be removed unless he has been given an opportunity of`
  line `being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (57639)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=57639&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Qualifications, terms and conditions of service of Chairperson, Judicial Member and`
  line `Expert Member.--Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the qualifications, appointment,`
  line `term of office, salaries and allowances, resignation, removal and other terms and conditions of service of`
  line `the Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member of the Tribunal appointed after the commencement`
  line `of ^2`
  line `[the Tribunals Reforms Act, 2021, shall be governed by the provisions of Chapter II of the said Act]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert Member appointed before the`
  line `commencement of Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017, shall continue to be governed by the`
  line `provisions of this Act, and the rules made thereunder as if the provisions of section 184 of the Finance`
  line `Act, 2017 had not come into force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 7 of 2017, s. 182 (w.e.f. 26-5-2017).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 33 of 2021, s. 27, for “Part XIV of Chapter VI of the Finance Act, 2017 (7 of 2017), shall be governed by the provisions of the section 184 of that Act” (w.e.f. 4-4-2021).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (3993)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `To act as Chairperson of Tribunal or to discharge his functions in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3993&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `In the event of the occurrence of any vacancy in the office of the Chairperson of the Tribunal, by reason`
  line `of his death, resignation or otherwise, such Judicial Member of the Tribunal as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, authorise in this behalf, shall act as the Chairperson until the date on which a new`
  line `Chairperson is appointed in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (3994)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Staff of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3994&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall determine the nature and categories of the`
  line `officers and other employees required to assist the Tribunal in the discharge of its functions.`
  line
  line `(2) The recruitment of the officers and other employees of the Tribunal shall be made by the`
  line `Chairperson in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The officers and other employees of the Tribunal shall discharge their functions under the general`
  line `superintendence of the Chairperson.`
  line
  line `(4) The salaries and allowances and conditions of service of the officers and other employees of the`
  line `Tribunal shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (3995)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Financial and administrative powers of Chairperson.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3995&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson of the Tribunal shall`
  line `exercise such financial and administrative powers as may be vested in him under the rules made by the`
  line `Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Chairperson may delegate such of his financial and administrative powers, as he`
  line `may think fit, to any Judicial Member or Expert Member or officer of the Tribunal subject to the`
  line `condition that the Member or such officer, while exercising such delegated power, continues to act under`
  line `the direction, control and supervision of the Chairperson.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (3996)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Tribunal to settle disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3996&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall have the jurisdiction over all civil cases`
  line `where a substantial question relating to environment (including enforcement of any legal right relating to`
  line `environment), is involved and such question arises out of the implementation of the enactments specified`
  line `in Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(2) The Tribunal shall hear the disputes arising from the questions referred to in sub-section (1) and`
  line `settle such disputes and pass order thereon.`
  line
  line `(3) No application for adjudication of dispute under this section shall be entertained by the Tribunal`
  line `unless it is made within a period of six months from the date on which the cause of action for such dispute`
  line `first arose:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from filing the application within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not exceeding`
  line `sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (3997)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Relief, compensation and restitution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3997&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal may, by an order, provide,--`
  line
  line `(a) relief and compensation to the victims of pollution and other environmental damage arising`
  line `under the enactments specified in the Schedule I (including accident occurring while handling any`
  line `hazardous substance);`
  line
  line `(b) for restitution of property damaged;`
  line
  line `(c) for restitution of the environment for such area or areas,`
  line
  line `as the Tribunal may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The relief and compensation and restitution of property and environment referred to in clauses (a),`
  line `(b) and (c) of sub-section (1) shall be in addition to the relief paid or payable under the Public Liability`
  line `Insurance Act, 1991 (6 of 1991).`
  line
  line `(3) No application for grant of any compensation or relief or restitution of property or environment`
  line `under this section shall be entertained by the Tribunal unless it is made within a period of five years from`
  line `the date on which the cause for such compensation or relief first arose:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the applicant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from filing the application within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not exceeding`
  line `sixty days.`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal may, having regard to the damage to public health, property and environment, divide`
  line `the compensation or relief payable under separate heads specified in Schedule II so as to provide`
  line `compensation or relief to the claimants and for restitution of the damaged property or environment, as it`
  line `may think fit.`
  line
  line `(5) Every claimant of the compensation or relief under this Act shall intimate to the Tribunal about`
  line `the application filed to, or, as the case may be, compensation or relief received from, any other court or`
  line authority.
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (3998)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Tribunal to have appellate jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3998&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by,--`
  line
  line `(a) an order or decision, made, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal`
  line `Act, 2010, by the appellate authority under section 28 of the Water (Prevention and Control of`
  line `Pollution) Act, 1974 (6 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(b) an order passed, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, by`
  line `the State Government under section 29 of the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974`
  line `(6 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(c) directions issued, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, by`
  line `a Board, under section 33A of the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution) Act, 1974 (6 of 1974);`
  line
  line `(d) an order or decision made, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act,`
  line `2010, by the appellate authority under section 13 of the Water (Prevention and Control of Pollution)`
  line `Cess Act, 1977 (36 of 1977);`
  line
  line `(e) an order or decision made, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act,`
  line `2010, by the State Government or other authority under section 2 of the Forest (Conservation) Act,`
  line `1980 (69 of 1980);`
  line
  line `(f) an order or decision, made, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act,`
  line `2010, by the Appellate Authority under section 31 of the Air (Prevention and Control of Pollution)`
  line `Act, 1981 (14 of 1981);`
  line
  line `(g) any direction issued, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010,`
  line `under section 5 of the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(h) an order made, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010,`
  line `granting environmental clearance in the area in which any industries, operations or processes or class`
  line `of industries, operations and processes shall not be carried out or shall be carried out subject to certain`
  line `safeguards under the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(i) an order made, on or after the commencement of the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010,`
  line `refusing to grant environmental clearance for carrying out any activity or operation or process under`
  line `the Environment (Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986);`
  line
  line `(j) any determination of benefit sharing or order made, on or after the commencement of the`
  line `National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, by the National Biodiversity Authority or a State Biodiversity`
  line `Board under the provisions of the Biological Diversity Act, 2002 (18 of 2003),`
  line
  line `may, within a period of thirty days from the date on which the order or decision or direction or`
  line `determination is communicated to him, prefer an appeal to the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed under this section within a further period`
  line `not exceeding sixty days.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (3999)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Liability to pay relief or compensation in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=3999&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where death of, or injury to, any`
  line `person (other than a workman) or damage to any property or environment has resulted from an accident`
  line `or the adverse impact of an activity or operation or process, under any enactment specified in Schedule I,`
  line `the person responsible shall be liable to pay such relief or compensation for such death, injury or damage,`
  line `under all or any of the heads specified in Schedule II, as may be determined by the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) If the death, injury or damage caused by an accident or the adverse impact of an activity or`
  line `operation or process under any enactment specified in Schedule I cannot be attributed to any single`
  line `activity or operation or process but is the combined or resultant effect of several such activities,`
  line `operations and processes, the Tribunal may, apportion the liability for relief or compensation amongst`
  line `those responsible for such activities, operations and processes on an equitable basis.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall, in case of an accident, apply the principle of no fault`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (4000)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Application or appeal to Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4000&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Each application under sections 14 and 15 or an`
  line `appeal under section 16 shall, be made to the Tribunal in such form, contain such particulars, and, be`
  line `accompanied by such documents and such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in section 16, an application for grant of relief or`
  line `compensation or settlement of dispute may be made to the Tribunal by--`
  line
  line `(a) the person, who has sustained the injury; or`
  line
  line `(b) the owner of the property to which the damage has been caused; or`
  line
  line `(c) where death has resulted from the environmental damage, by all or any of the legal`
  line `representatives of the deceased; or`
  line
  line `(d) any agent duly authorised by such person or owner of such property or all or any of the legal`
  line `representatives of the deceased, as the case may be; or`
  line
  line `(e) any person aggrieved, including any representative body or organisation; or`
  line
  line `(f) the Central Government or a State Government or a Union territory Administration or the`
  line `Central Pollution Control Board or a State Pollution Control Board or a Pollution Control Committee`
  line `or a local authority, or any environmental authority constituted or established under the Environment`
  line `(Protection) Act, 1986 (29 of 1986) or any other law for the time being in force:`
  line
  line `Provided that where all the legal representatives of the deceased have not joined in any such`
  line `application for compensation or relief or settlement of dispute, the application shall be made on`
  line `behalf of, or, for the benefit of all the legal representatives of the deceased and the legal`
  line `representatives who have not so joined shall be impleaded as respondents to the application:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the person, the owner, the legal representative, agent, representative body or`
  line `organisation shall not be entitled to make an application for grant of relief or compensation or`
  line `settlement of dispute if such person, the owner, the legal representative, agent, representative body or`
  line `organisation have preferred an appeal under section 16.`
  line
  line `(3) The application, or as the case may be, the appeal filed before the Tribunal under this Act shall be`
  line `dealt with by it as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the`
  line `application, or, as the case may be, the appeal, finally within six months from the date of filing of the`
  line `application, or as the case may be, the appeal, after providing the parties concerned an opportunity to be`
  line heard.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (4001)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title `Procedure and powers of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4001&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Tribunal shall not be bound by the procedure laid`
  line `down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) but shall be guided by the principles of natural`
  line justice.
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of this Act, the Tribunal shall have power to regulate its own procedure.`
  line
  line `(3) The Tribunal shall also not be bound by the rules of evidence contained in the Indian Evidence`
  line `Act, 1872 (1 of 1872).`
  line
  line `(4) The Tribunal shall have, for the purposes of discharging its functions under this Act, the same`
  line `powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a`
  line `suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) subject to the provisions of sections 123 and 124 of the Indian Evidence Act, 1872`
  line `(1 of 1872), requisitioning any public record or document or copy of such record or document from`
  line `any office;`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(f) reviewing its decision;`
  line
  line `(g) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(h) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte;`
  line
  line `(i) pass an interim order (including granting an injunction or stay) after providing the parties`
  line `concerned an opportunity to be heard, on any application made or appeal filed under this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) pass an order requiring any person to cease and desist from committing or causing any`
  line `violation of any enactment specified in Schedule I;`
  line
  line `(k) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) All proceedings before the Tribunal shall be deemed to be the judicial proceedings within the`
  line `meaning of sections 193, 219 and 228 for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of`
  line `1860) and the Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for the purposes of section 195 and Chapter`
  line `XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (4002)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title `Tribunal to apply certain principles.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4002&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The Tribunal shall, while passing any order or decision`
  line `or award, apply the principles of sustainable development, the precautionary principle and the polluter`
  line `pays principle.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (4003)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Decision to be taken by majority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4003&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The decision of the Tribunal by majority of Members shall`
  line `be binding:`
  line
  line `Provided that if there is a difference of opinion among the Members hearing an application or appeal,`
  line `and the opinion is equally divided, the Chairperson shall hear (if he has not heard earlier such application`
  line `or appeal) such application or appeal and decide:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the Chairperson himself has heard such application or appeal along with`
  line `other Members of the Tribunal, and if there is a difference of opinion among the Members in such cases`
  line `and the opinion is equally devided, he shall refer the matter to other Members of the Tribunal who shall`
  line `hear such application or appeal and decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (4004)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Appeal to Supreme Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4004&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by any award, decision or order of the`
  line `Tribunal, may, file an appeal to the Supreme Court, within ninety days from the date of communication of`
  line `the award, decision or order of the Tribunal, to him, on any one or more of the grounds specified in`
  line `section 100 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908):`
  line
  line `Provided that the Supreme Court may entertain any appeal after the expiry of ninety days, if it is`
  line `satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (4005)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title Cost.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4005&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) While disposing of an application or an appeal under this Act, the Tribunal shall have`
  line `power to make such order as to costs, as it may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the Tribunal holds that a claim is not maintainable, or is false or vexatious, and such claim`
  line `is disallowed, in whole or in part, the Tribunal may, if it so thinks fit, after recording its reasons for`
  line `holding such claim to be false or vexatious, make an order to award costs, including lost benefits due to`
  line `any interim injunction.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (4006)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Deposit of amount payable for damage to environment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4006&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any amount by way of`
  line `compensation or relief is ordered to be paid under any award or order made by the Tribunal on the ground`
  line `of any damage to environment, that amount shall be remitted to the authority specified under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 7A of the Public Liability Insurance Act, 1991 (6 of 1991) for being credited to`
  line `the Environmental Relief Fund established under that section.`
  line
  line `(2) The amount of compensation or relief credited to the Environmental Relief Fund under`
  line `sub-section (1), may, notwithstanding anything contained in the Public Liability Insurance Act, 1991`
  line `(6 of 1991) be utilised by such persons or authority, in such manner and for such purposes relating to`
  line `environment, as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (4007)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Execution of award or order or decision of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4007&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) An award or order or decision of`
  line `the Tribunal under this Act shall be executable by the Tribunal as a decree of a civil court, and for this`
  line `purpose, the Tribunal shall have all the powers of a civil court.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the Tribunal may transmit any order or`
  line `award made by it to a civil court having local jurisdiction and such civil court shall execute the order or`
  line `award as if it were a decree made by that court.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the person responsible, for death of, or injury to any person or damage to any property and`
  line `environment, against whom the award or order is made by the Tribunal, fails to make the payment or`
  line `deposit the amount as directed by the Tribunal within the period so specified in the award or order, such`
  line `amount, without prejudice to the filing of complaint for prosecution for an offence under this Act or any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, shall be recoverable from the aforesaid person as arrears of land`
  line `revenue or of public demand.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (4008)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with orders of Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4008&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever, fails to comply with`
  line `any order or award or decision of the Tribunal under this Act, he shall be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to three years, or with fine which may extend to ten crore rupees, or with`
  line `both and in case the failure or contravention continues, with additional fine which may extend to twentyfive`
  line `thousand rupees for every day during which such failure or contravention continues after conviction`
  line `for the first such failure or contravention:`
  line
  line `Provided that in case a company fails to comply with any order or award or a decision of the Tribunal`
  line `under this Act, such company shall be punishable with fine which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees,`
  line `and in case the failure or contravention continues, with additional fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line `rupees for every day during which such failure or contravention continues after conviction for the first`
  line `such failure or contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) every`
  line `offence under this Act shall be deemed to be non-cognizable within the meaning of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (4009)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4009&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was directly in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he had exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by the company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director" in relation to a firm means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (4010)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title `Offences by Government Department.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4010&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any Department of the Government fails to`
  line `comply with any order or award or decision of the Tribunal under this Act, the Head of the Department`
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of such failure and shall be liable to be proceeded against for having`
  line `committed an offence under this Act and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall render such Head of the Department liable to any`
  line `punishment if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a Department of the Government and it is proved that the offence has been committed with`
  line `the consent or connivance of, or is attributable to any neglect on the part of any officer, other than the`
  line `Head of the Department, such officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable`
  line `to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (4011)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 30
  title `Bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4011&sectionno=29&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from the date of establishment of the Tribunal under this`
  line `Act, no civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any appeal in respect of any matter, which the`
  line `Tribunal is empowered to determine under its appellate jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(2) No civil court shall have jurisdiction to settle dispute or entertain any question relating to any`
  line `claim for granting any relief or compensation or restitution of property damaged or environment damaged`
  line `which may be adjudicated upon by the Tribunal, and no injunction in respect of any action taken or to be`
  line `taken by or before the Tribunal in respect of the settlement of such dispute or any such claim for granting`
  line `any relief or compensation or restitution of property damaged or environment damaged shall be granted`
  line `by the civil court.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (4012)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 31
  title `Cognizance of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4012&sectionno=30&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence under this Act`
  line `except on a complaint made by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Central Government or any authority or officer authorised in this behalf by that`
  line `Government; or`
  line
  line `(b) any person who has given notice of not less than sixty days in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed, of the alleged offence and of his intention to make a complaint, to the Central`
  line `Government or the authority or officer authorised as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(2) No court inferior to that of a Metropolitan Magistrate or, a Judicial Magistrate of the first class`
  line `shall try any offence punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (4013)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 32
  title `Members and staff of Tribunal to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4013&sectionno=31&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `The Chairperson, the Judicial and`
  line `Expert Members, officers and other employees of the Tribunal shall be deemed to be public servants`
  line `within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (4014)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 33
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4014&sectionno=32&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the employees of the Central Government or a State Government or any statutory authority, for anything`
  line `which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made`
  line thereunder.
  line
  line `(2) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Chairperson or, Judicial`
  line `Member or Expert Member of the Tribunal or any other person authorised by the Chairperson or Judicial`
  line `Member or the Expert Member for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in`
  line `pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (4015)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 34
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4015&sectionno=33&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act, shall have effect notwithstanding`
  line `anything inconsistent contained in any other law for the time being in force or in any instrument having`
  line `effect by virtue of any law other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (4016)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 35
  title `Power to amend Schedule I.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4016&sectionno=34&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification, amend the`
  line `Schedule I by including therein any other Act, enacted by Parliament having regard to the objective of`
  line `environmental protection and conservation of natural resources, or omitting therefrom any Act already`
  line `specified therein and on the date of publication of such notification, such Act shall be deemed to be`
  line `included in or, as the case may be, omitted from the Schedule I.`
  line
  line `(2) A copy of every notification proposed to be issued under sub-section (1), shall be laid in draft`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `disapproving the issue of the notification or both Houses agree in making any modification in the`
  line `notification, the notification shall not be issued or, as the case may be, shall be issued only in such`
  line `modified form as may be agreed upon by both the Houses.`
obj_root_law_sections_34_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (4017)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 36
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4017&sectionno=35&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) rules as to the persons who shall be entitled to appear before the Tribunal under clause (a) of`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure for hearing applications and appeals and other matters pertaining to the`
  line `applications and appeals under clause (b) of sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(c) the minimum number of members who shall hear the applications and appeals in respect of`
  line `any class or classes of applications and appeals under clause (c) of sub-section (4) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(d) the transfer of cases by the Chairperson from one place of sitting (including the ordinary place`
  line `of sitting) to other place of sitting;`
  line
  line `(e) the selection committee and the manner of appointment of the Judicial Member and Expert`
  line `Member of the Tribunal under sub-section (3) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the salaries and allowances payable to, and other terms and conditions of service (including`
  line `pension, gratuity and other retirement benefits) of, the Chairperson, Judicial Member and Expert`
  line `Member of the Tribunal under section 9;`
  line
  line `(g) the procedure for inquiry of the charges against the Chairperson or Judicial Member of the`
  line `Tribunal under sub-section (4) of section 10;`
  line
  line `(h) the recruitment of officers and other employees of the Tribunal under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 12; and the salaries and allowances and other conditions of service of the officers and other`
  line `employees of the Tribunal under sub-section (4) of that section;`
  line
  line `(i) the financial and administrative powers to be exercised by the Chairperson of the Tribunal`
  line `under section 13;`
  line
  line `(j) the form of application or appeal, the particulars which it shall contain and the documents to`
  line `be accompanied by and the fees payable under sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(k) any such matter in respect of which the Tribunal shall have powers of a civil court under`
  line `clause (k) of sub-section (4) of section 19;`
  line
  line `(l) the manner and the purposes for which the amount of compensation or relief credited to the`
  line `Environment Relief Fund shall be utilised under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner of giving notice to make a complaint under clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 30;`
  line
  line `(n) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by rules or in respect of which`
  line `provision is to be made by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this Act by the Central Government shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (4018)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 37
  title `Amendment of certain enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4018&sectionno=36&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `The enactments specified in the Schedule III to this Act`
  line `shall be amended in the manner specified therein and such amendments shall take effect on the date of`
  line `establishment of the Tribunal.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (4019)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 38
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4019&sectionno=37&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government, may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary for removing the`
  line `difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made after the expiry of a period of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (4020)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 39
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004&sectionId=4020&sectionno=38&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_16_18_00009_201019_1517807326004
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `(1) The National Environment Tribunal Act, 1995 (27 of 1995) and the`
  line `National Environment Appellate Authority Act, 1997 (22 of 1997) are hereby repealed (hereinafter`
  line `referred to as the repealed Act).`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Acts shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) The National Environment Appellate Authority established under sub-section (1) of section 3 of`
  line `the National Environment Appellate Authority Act, 1997 (22 of 1997), shall, on the establishment of the`
  line `National Green Tribunal under the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, stand dissolved.`
  line
  line `(4) On the dissolution of the National Environment Appellate Authority established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the National Environment Appellate Authority Act, 1997 (22 of 1997), the`
  line `persons appointed as the Chairperson, Vice-chairperson and every other person appointed as Member of`
  line `the said National Environment Appellate Authority and holding office as such immediately before the`
  line `establishment of the National Green Tribunal under the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010, shall vacate`
  line `their respective offices and no such Chairperson, Vice-chairperson and every other person appointed as`
  line `Member shall be entitled to claim any compensation for the premature termination of the term of his`
  line `office or of any contract of service.`
  line
  line `(5) All cases pending before the National Environment Appellate Authority established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 3 of the National Environment Appellate Authority Act, 1997 (22 of 1997) on`
  line `or before the establishment of the National Green Tribunal under the National Green Tribunal Act, 2010,`
  line `shall, on such establishment, stand transferred to the said National Green Tribunal and the National Green`
  line `Tribunal shall dispose of such cases as if they were cases filed under that Act.`
  line
  line `(6) The officers or other employees who have been, immediately before the dissolution of the`
  line `National Environment Appellate Authority appointed on deputation basis to the National Environment`
  line `Appellate Authority, shall, on such dissolution, stand reverted to their parent cadre, Ministry or`
  line `Department, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(7) On the dissolution of the National Environment Appellate Authority, the officers and other`
  line `employees appointed on contract basis under the National Environment Appellate Authority and holding`
  line `office as such immediately before such dissolution, shall vacate their respective offices and such officers`
  line `and other employees shall be entitled to claim compensation for three months' pay and allowances or pay`
  line `and allowances for the remaining period of service, whichever is less, for the premature termination of`
  line `term of their office under their contract of service.`
  line
  line `(8) The mention of the particular matters referred to in sub-sections (2) to (7) shall not be held to`
  line `prejudice or affect the general application of section 6 of the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897) with`
  line `regard to the effect of repeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
